11 An Act relating to owners associations; amending 60
O.S. 2021, Section 854, which relates to owners
12 associations membership; requiring owners association
board members to be record owners of property in the
13 real estate development that the owners association
governs; requiring owners association board members
14 to physically reside in the real estate development
that the owners association governs; and providing an
15 effective date.
16
17
18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
19 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 60 O.S. 2021, Section 854, is
20 amended to read as follows:
21 Section 854. A. Membership of said owners association shall
22 consist of recorded owners of separately owned lots in the real
23 estate development. Membership is transferred upon legal transfer
24 of title to the separately owned lots. The owners association may
HB2588 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 also enforce the covenant and restrictions of the real estate
2 development when specified by the covenants and restrictions.
3 B. Board members of an owners association, after the real
4 estate developer relinquishes control of the owners association,
5 shall consist of members of said owners association that are current
6 recorded owners of lots in the real estate development.
7 Furthermore, owners association board members shall physically
8 reside in the real estate development that is governed by the said
9 owners association.
10 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
11
12 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON GOVERNMENT OVERSIGHT, dated
03/03/2026 - DO PASS, As Amended.
